
# Artificial Intelligence Course

## Course Description
This course provides an in-depth introduction to the field of Artificial Intelligence (AI). Students will learn the fundamental concepts, techniques, and algorithms used in AI, as well as their applications in various domains. Topics covered include machine learning, natural language processing, computer vision, and robotics. Emphasis will be placed on understanding the theoretical foundations and practical implementation of AI technologies.

## Course Topics
- Introduction to Artificial Intelligence
- Problem Solving and Search Algorithms
- Machine Learning: Supervised and Unsupervised Learning
- Neural Networks and Deep Learning
- Natural Language Processing
- Computer Vision
- Reinforcement Learning
- Ethics and Bias in AI
- AI Applications in Healthcare, Finance, and Robotics

## Course Objectives
By the end of this course, students will be able to:
- Understand the core concepts and theories in Artificial Intelligence.
- Apply various machine learning algorithms to solve real-world problems.
- Implement neural networks and deep learning models for AI applications.
- Analyze and process natural language data using AI techniques.
- Develop computer vision applications for image and video analysis.
- Explore ethical considerations and biases in AI systems.
- Apply AI algorithms in specific domains such as healthcare, finance, and robotics.

## Prerequisites
- Basic understanding of programming (preferably in Python)
- Familiarity with fundamental concepts of mathematics, including calculus and linear algebra
- Basic knowledge of data structures and algorithms

## Assessment Methods
- **Assignments:** Regular programming assignments to apply AI concepts.
- **Quizzes:** Short quizzes to assess understanding of theoretical concepts.
- **Midterm Exam:** A comprehensive exam covering topics taught in the first half of the course.
- **Final Project:** An AI project where students design and implement a practical AI application.
- **Class Participation:** Active participation in class discussions and group activities.

## Textbooks
- Stuart Russell and Peter Norvig, *Artificial Intelligence: A Modern Approach*, Pearson, 2021.
- Ian Goodfellow, Yoshua Bengio, and Aaron Courville, *Deep Learning*, MIT Press, 2016.

## Grading Policy
- Assignments: 30%
- Quizzes: 15%
- Midterm Exam: 20%
- Final Project: 25%
- Class Participation: 10%

